<TITLE> Chhatra Union leader arrested in Chittagong </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Sept 18 (bdnews24.com) Police picked up Chittagong University Chhatra Union president Monty Biswas from her home in the city Tuesday. Monty Biswas' younger sister Nandita Biswas told bdnews24.com that Monty was taken from their house at about 5.30pm. Police informed them that Monty was being taken to the Detective Branch office in the city, Nandita said. Hathazari police chief Mostafizur Rahman told bdnews24.com that Monty was arrested from her house in connection with the incidents of student protest and ransacking at Chittagong University in August. He said Monty would be produced in court Wednesday. Monty is a master's student in the department of oriental languages (Pali and Sanskrit) at Chittagong University. A case has been filed with Hathazari Police Station against 1,500 unnamed people in connection with the CU protests and ransacking. bdnews24.co
